The paper deals with an online learning problem and proposes a simple algorithm based on semidefinite programming. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Information Theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses clustering and ranking problems, which are common topics in Data Structures (cs.DS) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of entropy, which is a concept often studied in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.IT, followed by cs.DS, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
